SIMPLE: double-cross
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: double-cross
<hw>double-cross</hw></mhw> <pos>v. t.</pos>
<def>to betray or swindle (a colleague); to promise (a collaborator) one
thing and to treacherously do another, to the detriment of the
collaborator.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cross, betray.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>double-cross</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>double cross</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: double-cross
<hw>double-cross</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>the act of double-crossing; the betrayal or swindling of a
collaborator or colleague.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cross, betray.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>double-crosser</ent>⟦br⟧
